{
  "uuid": "hpqO",
  "titre": "Limite d'une suite dans $\\R^2$",
  "theme": "topologie",
  "auteur": "",
  "date": "",
  "organisation": "AMSCC",
  "contenu": [
    {
      "type": "texte",
      "value": "<p>Pour tout <span class=\"math inline\">\\(k \\in \\N\\)</span>, on pose <span class=\"math display\">\\[X_k = \\left(\\frac{2}{1+k} , 1+e^{-k} \\right) \\in \\R^2\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\ell = (0,1)\\)</span>. Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2}\\)</span> où <span class=\"math inline\">\\(||.||_{2}\\)</span> est la norme euclidienne.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2} = \\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{2}{1+k}\\right)^2 + \\left(e^{-k}\\right)^2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{(1+k)^2} + e^{-2k} }\\)</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>En déduire la convergence de la suite <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X_k)\\)</span> dans <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\R^2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2} \\xrightarrow[k \\to +\\infty]{}0\\)</span> donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X_k \\xrightarrow[k \\to +\\infty]{}\\ell\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    }
  ]
}